Lexical Analysis Lexical Analysis Tokens &lt;token, value&gt;
 token = unique integer value, e.g. ID = 1, INT = 2 value (optional) = data related to token, e.g. &ldquo;x&rdquo;, 5  Hence, we have &lt;ID, &ldquo;x&rdquo;&gt;, &lt;INT, 5&gt;
